<image 1>The idges indicated with a rows are:

A. aretes
B. eskers
C. a hanging valley
D. lateral moraines

The ridges indicated with arrows in the image are:

A. aretes

Aretes are sharp, narrow ridges that form when two or more cirques cut into a mountain peak, leaving a knife-edge ridge between them. The image shows these sharp ridges, which are characteristic of aretes.
